nESPNU Inside the Polls
tESPNU Inside the Polls is a television program that breaks down the latest college football polls. The program airs every Monday for one hour from 6pm ET to 7pm ET on ESPNU during the college football season. Since debuting on September 5, 2005, the host has been ESPNU signature anchor Mike Hall along with analysis from former head coach Mike Gottfried and ESPN's Scout's Inc. analyst Todd McShay. Its official name is ESPNU Inside the Polls presented by Conoco.\n\nThe show was originally named The U:Inside the Polls, but was changed before the 2006 college football season. The show breaks down the latest college football polls in contrast to the performance of those teams on Saturday. ESPNU Inside the Polls is broadcast at the ESPNU headquarters in Charlotte, North Carolina and was one of the first studio programs to air on the network.
